Introduction

Lee Seoan, formerly known as Lee Soomi or Soomi, is a South Korean singer, rapper, and actress under Ghost Studio. She debuted as the main dancer and rapper of the Korean Pop female trio SeeYa.

On July 23, 2010, Lee Soomi left SeeYa to be the leader of the new Core Contents Media mixed group Co-ed School and its sub-unit F-VE DOLLS. On February 17, 2012, Soomi left Co-ed School to focus on her solo career. In 2013 she joined D-Business Entertainment.
